[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926820&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926820&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Friends -

     I couldn't give a hoot what the order of names are (high-first, as in
the UK, or low-first, as in everywhere else).  Why can't we settle on some
order that we can all be happy with and be done with it?  I thought we were
engineers, not interior decorators!  Why then are we bickering about which
ordering to use?

     Jon is 1000% correct in his opposition to reserving top-level names
from being used in low-level names.  What a ridiculous idea!  Who, may
I ask, is going to maintain this charming list and how is it going to be
enforced?

     Let's do one of two things: we in the US/top-level-last camp say we
picked the wrong order and migrate to top-level-first, OR our friends in
the UK/top-level-first camp say they picked the wrong order and migrate to
top-level-last.  A third alternative is for our friends in the UK to
accept the fact that they're incompatible and put up with the consequences
of their decision to be incompatible.

-- Mark -- "I'd rather switch than fight"
